# automatically routes compileNimble to worker_<pid>/ via .biome_get_compile_dir
# which detects worker context from BIOME_WORKER_MODE env var.
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# SECTION R7: biome_make_cluster() — export BIOME_RUN_ID to workers
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# This is the patch users should add to the existing biome_make_cluster
# function in the main Rprofile_site.R.template. The env_vec must include:
#
#   BIOME_RUN_ID = Sys.getenv("BIOME_RUN_ID"),
#   BIOME_RUN_TIMESTAMP = Sys.getenv("BIOME_RUN_TIMESTAMP"),
#
# This propagation is REQUIRED so workers create their compile subdirs
# under the same run folder as the master.
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

